00:39:24.500 --> 00:39:28.260 align:middle line:84%
in the world and their place in
the world, to idolize poverty.

00:39:28.260 --> 00:39:30.710 align:middle line:84%
And often times there's
no dignity in poverty,

00:39:30.710 --> 00:39:33.200 align:middle line:84%
because all your options
are stripped away.

00:39:33.200 --> 00:39:35.960 align:middle line:84%
When you don't have food
to eat or a place to live,

00:39:35.960 --> 00:39:38.580 align:middle line:84%
that's very devastating on
a soul level to a person.

00:39:38.580 --> 00:39:39.380 align:middle line:90%
>> KRAMER: Yeah.

00:39:39.380 --> 00:39:42.890 align:middle line:84%
Again, a very unforgiving
view in my supernal pathway

00:39:42.890 --> 00:39:46.430 align:middle line:84%
to that, which is I get
it and it's not funny.

00:39:46.430 --> 00:39:48.690 align:middle line:84%
And I've brushed with
it once or twice.

00:39:48.690 --> 00:39:50.510 align:middle line:84%
But it always shows
one thing, which

00:39:50.510 --> 00:39:52.167 align:middle line:90%
is you're out of alignment.

00:39:52.167 --> 00:39:53.750 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: It's the
poverty in spirit.

00:39:53.750 --> 00:39:56.810 align:middle line:84%
>> KRAMER: It's a misalignment
with what you're doing and what

00:39:56.810 --> 00:39:58.099 align:middle line:90%
you should be doing.

00:39:58.099 --> 00:40:00.140 align:middle line:84%
What you're capable of
doing and what you believe

00:40:00.140 --> 00:40:01.470 align:middle line:90%
you're capable of doing.

00:40:01.470 --> 00:40:03.470 align:middle line:84%
Where there's a disconnect
that poverty is there

00:40:03.470 --> 00:40:08.270 align:middle line:84%
to show you the uncertainty
and the trepidation

00:40:08.270 --> 00:40:11.810 align:middle line:84%
in that terrible fear
that some people have,

00:40:11.810 --> 00:40:15.122 align:middle line:84%
which is am I going to end
up with nothing on the street

00:40:15.122 --> 00:40:16.330 align:middle line:90%
with a little cardboard sign?

00:40:16.330 --> 00:40:18.955 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Or am I going to end
up that jerk in the mansion who

00:40:18.955 --> 00:40:19.790 align:middle line:90%
cares about no one?

00:40:19.790 --> 00:40:21.890 align:middle line:84%
>> KRAMER: Or am I going to be
a lonely person in a big empty

00:40:21.890 --> 00:40:22.490 align:middle line:90%
house?

00:40:22.490 --> 00:40:23.150 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Exactly.

00:40:23.150 --> 00:40:23.540 align:middle line:90%
>> KRAMER: Right.

00:40:23.540 --> 00:40:26.180 align:middle line:84%
So both of those things come
from the same place, which is

00:40:26.180 --> 00:40:28.970 align:middle line:90%
as you say a poverty of spirit.

00:40:28.970 --> 00:40:32.180 align:middle line:84%
But I know lots of good
people who were in poverty.

00:40:32.180 --> 00:40:35.780 align:middle line:84%
And it would be tough for me
to say that their problem is

00:40:35.780 --> 00:40:37.160 align:middle line:90%
poverty of spirit.

00:40:37.160 --> 00:40:39.530 align:middle line:90%
Their challenge is misalignment.

00:40:39.530 --> 00:40:42.942 align:middle line:84%
What they're doing,
they think they

00:40:42.942 --> 00:40:44.650 align:middle line:84%
should be doing,
because that's what they

00:40:44.650 --> 00:40:46.210 align:middle line:90%
have to do to make it happen.

00:40:46.210 --> 00:40:48.490 align:middle line:84%
They don't believe that
they can do something

00:40:48.490 --> 00:40:51.730 align:middle line:84%
that they enjoy that
is a contribution

00:40:51.730 --> 00:40:54.620 align:middle line:84%
and that the world will ally
with them to support them

00:40:54.620 --> 00:40:55.420 align:middle line:90%
in that endeavor.

00:40:55.420 --> 00:40:56.605 align:middle line:90%
They don't believe it.

00:40:56.605 --> 00:40:58.730 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: There's a kind
of fatalism in that case,

00:40:58.730 --> 00:41:00.930 align:middle line:84%
that they won't be supported
in their best efforts.

00:41:00.930 --> 00:41:02.846 align:middle line:84%
>> KRAMER: There's just
this voice-- exactly--

00:41:02.846 --> 00:41:05.500 align:middle line:84%
there's just this voice saying,
that's for other people.

00:41:05.500 --> 00:41:06.910 align:middle line:90%
This guy, well, he's got this.

00:41:06.910 --> 00:41:07.710 align:middle line:90%
You haven't.

00:41:07.710 --> 00:41:10.360 align:middle line:84%
This woman, she's got these
things, but you haven't.

00:41:10.360 --> 00:41:13.210 align:middle line:84%
You're just going to have to
do this little job that you

00:41:13.210 --> 00:41:16.510 align:middle line:84%
don't like, it sucks, but you
can pay the rent just about.

00:41:16.510 --> 00:41:18.430 align:middle line:90%
And maybe one day, you'll win.

00:41:18.430 --> 00:41:20.620 align:middle line:84%
You'll scratch a card
in the gas station

00:41:20.620 --> 00:41:22.165 align:middle line:90%
and win a million dollars.

00:41:22.165 --> 00:41:23.530 align:middle line:90%
But probably not.

00:41:23.530 --> 00:41:28.600 align:middle line:84%
So that is put into people
through mainstream culture.

00:41:28.600 --> 00:41:31.570 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: I was going to say
both these points of views have

00:41:31.570 --> 00:41:33.880 align:middle line:84%
been programmed into
us with intention.

00:41:33.880 --> 00:41:34.780 align:middle line:90%
>> KRAMER: Yeah.

00:41:34.780 --> 00:41:37.690 align:middle line:84%
And if you always look
at-- it's really simple--

00:41:37.690 --> 00:41:40.295 align:middle line:84%
always look at the great
leadership of the world

00:41:40.295 --> 00:41:41.095 align:middle line:90%
